    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-03-04T05:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-03-04T05:00:00-05:00" n="137"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d137">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">660F.116/159: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Czechoslovakia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Wright</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Praha</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-03-04T11:00:00+01:00"
                            >March 4, 1935—11 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received March 4—9:56 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>11. My telegram No. 9, February 19, 4 p.m. Foreign Office now informs me that
                    Czech-German Clearing Committee has determined to recommend to respective
                    Governments that part payments in marks for cotton be at rate 2½ percent and for
                    other shipments upon percentage basis equivalent to expenses attendant all
                    transactions.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wright</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
